Navigation revamp: sidebar-first workspace with command palette, breadcrumbs, and keyboard shortcuts

Replaces the duplicated TopNav-plus-Sidebar nav pattern on app pages with a
modern sidebar-first workspace shell modeled after Linear, Vercel, and Notion.
Public pages (/, /r/[id], /offline) keep the marketing-style top nav unchanged.

App shell layout (app/(app)/layout.tsx)
- New sticky 56px AppTopBar: hamburger (mobile only), brand logo, breadcrumbs,
  "Search Chronicle..." trigger button with cross-platform Cmd/Ctrl K hint,
  shortcuts help icon.
- New AppSidebar (240px expanded, 64px icon-only): brand-gradient "+ New
  research" CTA, primary nav (Research/History/Visualizations) with shortcut
  hints, Recent sessions section (top 5 from /api/conversations with shimmer
  skeleton), secondary nav (Settings/About), collapse toggle. Active state
  shows a gradient pill plus a left-edge accent bar. On mobile becomes a
  slide-in drawer with overlay.
- Persists sidebar collapsed state in localStorage via SSR-safe hook.

New components under src/components/nav/
- AppSidebar.tsx + AppSidebar.css
- AppTopBar.tsx + AppTopBar.css
- Breadcrumbs.tsx + Breadcrumbs.css (auto-derives from pathname; collapses
  to last 2 crumbs on mobile)
- CommandPalette.tsx + CommandPalette.css (4 groups: Go to / Actions /
  Starter queries / Recent research; arrow-key navigation; backdrop blur;
  animated entrance; ESC to close)
- ShortcutsHelp.tsx + ShortcutsHelp.css (overlay listing every shortcut)

New hooks under src/hooks/ (all client-side, SSR-safe)
- useLocalStorage<T>: hydration-safe persistence
- useMediaQuery: tracks (max-width: 900px) for mobile drawer
- useRecentSessions(limit): fetches top N from /api/conversations
- useGlobalShortcuts: window keydown listener with leader-key pattern;
  skips firing when focus is inside editable fields (input, textarea,
  contenteditable, role=textbox/combobox)

Keyboard shortcuts
- Cmd/Ctrl+K        open command palette
- ?                 show shortcuts help
- ESC               close any overlay or drawer
- N                 new research
- G then R/H/V/S/A/I  navigate to research / history / visualizations /
                       settings / about / landing
- Up/Down + Enter   inside palette: navigate + run

Accessibility (per ui-ux-pro-max skill recommendations)
- aria-current="page" on the active sidebar item
- aria-modal + aria-label on the palette and shortcuts dialogs
- aria-hidden on every decorative SVG icon
- All icon-only buttons have aria-label
- Sidebar uses <aside aria-label="Workspace navigation"> with nested
  <nav aria-label="Primary"|"Secondary">
- Active state has both color and a structural left-bar (color is not the
  only signal)
- Skip link still first focusable
- prefers-reduced-motion respected on shimmer, palette pop-in, transitions

Cleanup
- Removed src/components/Sidebar.tsx + Sidebar.css (replaced by AppSidebar).
- Marketing TopNav still used by LandingPage and ShareableReport; renamed
  in commentary as the "marketing variant" while AppTopBar is the workspace
  variant.

E2E tests
- Updated navigation.spec.ts for the new sidebar-first selectors plus a
  breadcrumbs test.
- New command-palette.spec.ts (10 tests) covering Cmd/Ctrl+K open, ESC close,
  search trigger button, type-to-filter, Enter runs top match, ArrowDown +
  Enter, empty state, the help icon, G+H, G+A.
- seo-a11y.spec.ts: added sidebar ARIA-label test plus aria-current=page
  active-item test.
- Total suite: 41 -> 52 tests, all passing against the live deployment in
  about 1.4 min.

Live URL:  https://deep-research.intelliforge.tech (SW cache bumped to v7)
